    21	## Proposal 21: Zero Clustering Truncation
    22	
    23	### Mathematical Idea
    24	The Riemann explicit formula requires summing over all nontrivial zeta zeros:
    25	π(x) = R(x) − Σ_ρ R(x^ρ)
    26	
    27	If zeros exhibit correlated contributions due to GUE spacing statistics, we can group them into clusters and represent each cluster by a weighted representative. If cluster count grows as O(log(x)^C), we achieve polylog.
    28	
    29	### Key Conjecture
    30	The oscillatory sum S(x) = Σ_γ x^{iγ}/ρ converges within O(1) using O(log(x)^C) representative zeros.
